# P2P Audit Trail Rule

## Requirement
Every workflow in the TLCG P2P system that changes the status of a document **must**
call `_appendAuditLog_()` immediately after writing the new status to the sheet and
calling `SpreadsheetApp.flush()`.

This creates an immutable, append-only event log — one row per action — that can be
inspected in Google Sheets without touching the source record.

## Pattern

```javascript
// 1. Write the new status to the source sheet (in-place update as usual)
sheet.getRange(rowIndex, STATUS_COL).setValue(newStatus);
sheet.getRange(rowIndex, METADATA_COL).setValue(JSON.stringify(metadata));
SpreadsheetApp.flush();

// 2. Immediately append to the audit log (NEVER skip this step)
_appendAuditLog_({
  sheetName:  '<FLOW>_Audit_Log',   // e.g. 'PR_Audit_Log', 'AM_Audit_Log', 'PMT_Audit_Log'
  docNo:      docNo,                // document number: PR No, AM No, PMT No, …
  flow:       '<FLOW>',             // short code: 'PR' | 'AM' | 'PMT' | …
  company:    companyName,
  action:     '<ACTION>',           // 'Submit' | 'Approve' | 'Reject' | 'Return' | 'Resubmit'
  role:       '<ROLE>',             // 'requester' | 'budget' | 'supplier' | 'contract' | 'purchasing' | 'deptHead' | …
  actorEmail: actorEmail,
  actorName:  actorName || '',      // optional — leave '' if not available
  prevStatus: currentStatus,        // status BEFORE this action
  newStatus:  newStatus,            // status AFTER this action
  note:       note || '',           // rejection reason / approval note
  extra:      { /* optional structured extras */ }
});
```

## Audit log sheet schema (auto-created by _appendAuditLog_ if missing)

| Col | Header        | Description                                  |
|-----|---------------|----------------------------------------------|
| A   | Document No   | PR No / AM No / PMT No etc.                  |
| B   | Flow          | Short flow code: PR, AM, PMT …               |
| C   | Company       | Company name                                 |
| D   | Action        | Submit / Approve / Reject / Return / Resubmit|
| E   | Role          | Actor's role in this approval step           |
| F   | Actor Email   | Email of the person who triggered the action |
| G   | Actor Name    | Display name (may be empty)                  |
| H   | Prev Status   | Status string before the action              |
| I   | New Status    | Status string after the action               |
| J   | Timestamp     | ISO 8601 UTC string (auto-set by helper)     |
| K   | Note          | Approval note / rejection reason             |
| L   | Extra (JSON)  | Serialised extra data (sig URL, step, etc.)  |

## Rules for every new flow

1. **One `_<FLOW>_Audit_Log` sheet per flow** — named `<FLOW>_Audit_Log`
   (e.g. `PMT_Audit_Log`). The helper auto-creates it.
2. **Call `_appendAuditLog_()` for every action** that changes document status:
   - Submit / create
   - Every approve step (each approver role gets its own row)
   - Reject
   - Return / send-back
   - Resubmit
3. **Never call it conditionally** — the helper swallows its own errors so it
   will never break the main flow.
4. **Never delete or overwrite audit log rows** — the log is append-only. If a
   correction is needed, append a new "Correction" action row instead.

## Existing implementations (for reference)

| Flow | Audit Log Sheet   | Handlers wired                                   |
|------|-------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| PR   | `PR_Audit_Log`    | submit, approve (4 roles), reject, return, resubmit |
| AM   | `AM_Audit_Log`    | create, approve (deptHead), reject (deptHead)    |

When implementing **Payment Request (PMT)** or any future flow, follow the exact
same pattern above.
